-- Cameron Says U.K. Plans to Play Active Role in EU; Country Won't Join Euro
-- Kevin Costelloe
-- 2010-06-17T06:44:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/cameron-says-u-k-plans-to-play-active-role-in-eu-country-won-t-join-euro.html

          
          
             U.K. Prime Minister David Cameron
said today that his country plans to have a positive and active
role in the European Union. Speaking at a Brussels news
conference, Cameron said the U.K. will not become a member of
the euro area.  
          
          


  


        